workflow.name: Expense Logging with Telegram to Google Sheets using AI Voice & Text Parsing
workflow.description:
## Use Cases
-Personal or family budget tracking.

-Small business expense logging via Telegram

-Hands-free logging (using voice messages)

---

## How it works:

-Trigger receives text or voice.

-Optional branch transcribes audio to text.

-AI parses into a structured array (SOP enforces schema).

-Split Out produces 1 item per expense.

-Loop Over Items appends rows sequentially with a Wait, preventing missed writes.

-In parallel, Item Lists (Aggregate) builds a single summary string; Merge (Wait for Both) releases one final Telegram confirmation.

----

## Setup Instructions 

1. Connect credentials: Telegram, Google, OpenAI.
2. Sheets: Create a sheet with headers Date, Category, Merchant, Amount, Note. Copy Spreadsheet ID + sheet name.
3. Map columns in Append to Google Sheet.
4. Pick models: set Chat model (e.g., gpt-4o-mini) and Whisper for transcription if using audio.
5. Wait time: keep 500‚Äì1000 ms to avoid API race conditions.
6. Run: Send a Telegram message like:
Gas 34.67, Groceries 82.45, Coffee 6.25, Lunch 14.90.

----
## Customization ideas:

-Add categories map (Memory/Set) for consistent labeling.

-Add currency detection/formatting.

-Add error-to-Telegram path for invalid schema.

parameters.text:
=You are Expense Parser. Your job is to read a message describing one or more expenses and return ONLY a valid JSON array of objects for a Google Sheet with columns: Date, Category, Merchant, Amount, Note.

Each object must look like:
{
  "Date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "Category": "Food & Drink" | "Entertainment" | "Groceries" | "Transport" | "Fuel" | "Rent" | "Health" | "Shopping" | "Travel" | "Utilities" | "Income" | "Other",
  "Merchant": "string or null",
  "Amount": number,
  "Note": "string or null"
}

Rules:
- Date = today if not given (use {{ $now.toFormat('yyyy-MM-dd') }}).
- Amount: numbers only (strip $ or commas).
- Category: infer best match or "Other".
- Merchant: short name if mentioned.
- Note: short context like "Lunch", "Gas", "Movie tickets".
If no valid expenses, return [].

Output MUST be ONLY a JSON array matching the schema. No prose or code fences
User message: {{ $('Telegram Message Trigger').item.json.message.text }}
Audio User Message: {{ $json.text }}

parameters.content:
### üõ†Ô∏è Troubleshooting  
- **Missing rows?** Increase the Wait time to 800‚Äì1200 ms.  
- **AI returns no expenses?** Check that your message includes numbers and merchants.  
- **Google Sheets errors?** Confirm spreadsheet ID, sheet name, and column mapping.  
- **Audio not transcribing?** Ensure Whisper is selected in the transcription node.

### üîß Setup Instructions  
1. Connect credentials: **Telegram**, **Google**, **OpenAI**.  
2. Create a Google Sheet with headers:  
   `Date | Category | Merchant | Amount | Note`  
3. Copy your Sheet ID + Sheet name.  
4. Map the columns correctly in the **Append to Google Sheet** node.  
5. Pick models:  
   - Chat model: `gpt-4o-mini` (recommended)  
   - Audio transcription: Whisper (for voice notes)  
6. Keep the **Wait** node at `500‚Äì1000 ms` to avoid API race conditions.  
7. Test by sending a message like:  
   `Gas 34.67, Groceries 82.45, Coffee 6.25, Lunch 14.90`

### üìå Purpose  
Log multiple expenses directly from Telegram into Google Sheets ‚Äî using either text or audio messages.

This workflow is for anyone who wants a **fast, low-effort way to track expenses** without opening a spreadsheet or app. You simply send a quick message (or voice note) like:

`Groceries 82.45, Coffee 6.25, Uber 14.90`

and each item is automatically parsed and saved as its own row.

**Who this helps:**  
- Busy entrepreneurs  
- Freelancers and contractors  
- People who track business expenses manually  
- Anyone who prefers capturing expenses on the go  
- Users who don‚Äôt want to build a full accounting system

**Why this is useful:**  
- It replaces the repetitive task of entering expenses manually  
- Voice notes let you log hands-free while driving or moving  
- AI extracts multiple expenses from a single message, saving time  
- Google Sheets keeps your data accessible, editable, and exportable  
- Works instantly from your phone through Telegram

**Why download this template:**  
It gives you a ready-made, reliable system for expense tracking with **zero manual data entry**, using AI and simple messaging. No accounting software needed ‚Äî just Telegram and a Google Sheet.

### üé§ Telegram Input & Transcription  
This section receives a Telegram message, detects if it's audio, and transcribes it when needed.

Why: We want the user to be able to log expenses hands-free through **text or voice**, so both inputs flow into the same text-processing path.

### ü§ñ AI Parsing & Expense Extraction  
This section uses AI to identify all expenses in the message, splits them into individual items, and prepares them for Google Sheets.

Why: A single message may contain several expenses ‚Äî AI helps extract structured fields reliably.

### üìä Write to Sheets & Send Confirmation  
This section loops through each expense, writes it to Google Sheets, builds a summary, and sends a confirmation back to Telegram.

Why: Users need quick feedback that everything was recorded correctly.

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
